# Logical Units Structure

Use this rule for all components in `src/frontend/components/logical-units`.

## Component file contract

- Each component `*.tsx` file must export one and only one React component.
- Component files must use named exports only.
- Do not use default exports in component files.

## Required directory layout

- A component must live in a directory named after the component.
- The component directory must contain:
  - `<ComponentName>.tsx`
  - `index.ts`
- The barrel file must re-export from the component file using named export syntax:
  - `export * from './<ComponentName>'`

## Owned child components

- If a component owns child components, place them under:
  - `<ComponentName>/components/<ChildName>/`
- Each child component directory follows the same contract:
  - `<ChildName>.tsx`
  - `index.ts`
- This structure is recursive for nested ownership:
  - `<ChildName>/components/<GrandChildName>/...`

## Types and interfaces

- If a component defines component-local types or interfaces, place them in:
  - `<ComponentName>.types.ts`
- The `*.types.ts` file must export those declarations.
- The component file should import those types from the colocated `*.types.ts` file.

## Optional files

- Styles are optional. If present, keep them colocated with the component
  (for example `<ComponentName>.styles.scss`).

## Example structure

```text
src/frontend/components/logical-units/
|-- VideoPanel/
|   |-- VideoPanel.tsx
|   |-- VideoPanel.types.ts
|   |-- VideoPanel.styles.scss
|   |-- index.ts
|   `-- components/
|       `-- DeviceSettingsDialog/
|           |-- DeviceSettingsDialog.tsx
|           |-- DeviceSettingsDialog.types.ts
|           |-- DeviceSettingsDialog.styles.scss
|           |-- index.ts
|           `-- components/
|               `-- MicLevelBar/
|                   |-- MicLevelBar.tsx
|                   |-- MicLevelBar.types.ts
|                   |-- MicLevelBar.styles.scss
|                   |-- index.ts
|                   `-- components/
|                       `-- Bar/
|                           |-- Bar.tsx
|                           |-- Bar.styles.scss
|                           |-- Bar.types.ts
|                           `-- index.ts
```
